@page "/help"

<div class="page-stack">
    <header class="page-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Reference</p>
        <h1>Help</h1>
        <p>Quick reference for common questions about Media Tools Next.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="panel help-panel">
        <h2>Source and files</h2>
        <details><summary>What happens to source files?</summary><p>Source files are read for validation. The app does not modify, move, rename, or delete originals.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What is copied?</summary><p>Copy modes copy only selected outcomes to target folders: valid, corrupt, unknown, and error.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What do the check levels mean?</summary><p>Quick checks file headers only. Medium adds ImageMagick metadata validation. In-depth asks ImageMagick to fully read the image pixel data.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What do limits count?</summary><p>Limits count matched files only. In image-only mode, max files means max image files. Set any limit to 0 to disable it.</p></details>
    </section>

    <section class="panel help-panel">
        <h2>External tools</h2>
        <details><summary>Which external tools are used?</summary><p>ffmpeg and ffprobe for video and audio validation; ImageMagick (magick) for deep image checks; qpdf for PDF validation. All are optional — the app falls back to header checks if a tool is missing.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How do I install the tools?</summary>
            <p>Run in PowerShell (requires Chocolatey):</p>
            <pre><code>choco install ffmpeg imagemagick qpdf -y</code></pre>
            <p>ImageMagick is also probed under Program Files when <code>magick</code> is not on PATH.</p>
        </details>
        <details><summary>How do I verify tools are found?</summary><p>Go to the Validation step — the tool row at the top shows each tool as green (found) or red (missing). Hover a badge to see the resolved path.</p></details>
    </section>

    <section class="panel help-panel">
        <h2>Output and export</h2>
        <details><summary>What export formats are available?</summary><p>CSV produces a full structured file with all fields. TXT produces a tab-separated plain text file with status, category, path, and detail columns.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Where is the scan database stored?</summary><p>By default, sessions are stored in <code>%LocalAppData%\media-tools-next\media-tools-next.db</code>. You can override the path via the CLI <code>--db</code> flag.</p></details>
    </section>
</div>
